**Iran's Threat to Attack Israel: New Information and US General's Visit**
Iran has threatened to retaliate against Israel for the death of Ismail Haniyeh, the political leader of Hamas, who was killed in Tehran on July 31. Hamas has accused Israel of assassinating Haniyeh. According to Axios, Iran may attack Israel as early as Monday, August 5, or on August 12 or 13, during the Jewish holiday of Tisha B'Av. Three American and Israeli officials expect an attack to occur on August 5. The plans for the attack are reportedly finalized and accepted at the political level. Meanwhile, US Central Command chief Michael Kurilla has arrived in the Middle East and will visit Israel, countries in the Persian Gulf, and Jordan. Kurilla's visit was planned before the recent escalation of the conflict, but he may use the opportunity to 'mobilize the same international and regional coalition that defended Israel against Iran's attack on April 13.' On that day, Iran launched hundreds of rockets and drones at Israel in retaliation for Israel's bombing of an Iranian consulate in Damascus.
