**US Prepares for Potential Iranian Attack on Israel**
The US is preparing for a potential Iranian attack on Israel, following the assassination of Hamas' political bureau chief Ismail Haniyeh. According to Axios, US General Michael Kurilla's visit to the Middle East on August 3, 2024, was planned before the recent escalation, but it is expected that he will use his visit to mobilize the same international and regional coalition that defended Israel in a previous Iranian attack on April 13, 2024. US and Israeli officials expect the Iranian attack on Israel to occur on Monday. The US Department of Defense has reinforced its forces in the Middle East, anticipating a potential Iranian attack against Israel, with more warships and fighter jets. According to a US official, any retaliatory operation from Iran is expected to follow the same pattern as the previous attack on April 13, but with a larger scope. The Hezbollah party in Lebanon is also expected to participate in the potential Iranian attack on Israel. The Biden administration has expressed concern that mobilizing the same international and regional coalition that defended Israel in the previous attack may be more difficult now due to Haniyeh's assassination in the context of Israel's war on Gaza, which has sparked anti-Israel sentiment throughout the region. US General Michael Kurilla is expected to visit several Gulf states, Jordan, and Israel. Jordan will be a key stop on his trip, as it played a crucial role in the previous attack on April 13, 2024, by intercepting Iranian drones and allowing US and Israeli planes to use its airspace to intercept Iranian planes, according to a US official.
