**Houthis Launch Deadly Attack on Israel, Targeting Tel Aviv**
The Houthis, backed by Iran, launched their first deadly attack on Israel since November 2023, targeting Tel Aviv and killing one person and injuring four others. The attack was carried out by a drone, which the Israeli army believes was made in Iran. The Houthis claimed responsibility for the attack, saying it was a response to Israel's aggression against the Palestinians. The attack was part of a series of Houthi attacks on ships in the Red Sea, Gulf of Aden, and Indian Ocean, which have targeted ships linked to Israel, as well as American and British vessels. The Houthis have also claimed to have attacked Israeli ports and naval vessels in the Mediterranean. The Israeli army has accused the Houthis of being responsible for the attacks, which have caused significant damage and disruption to global trade. The Houthis have also been accused of being responsible for the detention of several ships, including the 'Galaxy Leader', which was seized in November 2023 and taken to the port of Al-Salif in Yemen. The Houthis have also been accused of being responsible for the detention of several ships, including the 'Galaxy Leader', which was seized in November 2023 and taken to the port of Al-Salif in Yemen.
